===Etymology 1===
Apparently from {{der|en|nds|-}} and {{der|en|gml|jolle}}, or {{der|en|nl|jol}}, possibly ultimately from a {{der|en|gem-pro|-}} derivative of {{der|en|ine-pro|*h₂ewlos||tube}}, see also {{cog|lt|aulas}}, {{cog|no|aul}}, {{cog|hit|||tube-shaped organ in the neck|tr=auli-}}, {{cog|sq|hollë}}, {{cog|la|alvus}}.<ref>{{R:ine:IEW|205}}</ref>
====Noun====
{{en-noun}}
# A small ship's boat, usually rowed by four or six oars.
# A [[fore-and-aft]] [[rig|rigged]] [[sailing vessel]] with two masts, main and [[mizzen]], the mizzen [[stepped]] [[abaft]] the [[rudder]] post.
#* {{quote-journal|1=en|year=1899|month=Feb|author=Joseph Conrad|authorlink=Joseph Conrad|title=The Heart of Darkness|journal=Blackwood's Edinburgh Magazine|page=193|passage=
The &ldquo;Nellie,&rdquo; a cruising '''yawl''', swung to her anchor without a flutter of the sails, and was at rest.}}
